&lt;p&gt;The Behavioral Health Registered Nurse (RN) provides comprehensive mental health care to patients in need of psychiatric and mental health support. The RN collaborates with a multidisciplinary team to assess, plan, implement, and evaluate individualized patient care plans. This role requires strong clinical skills, compassion, and the ability to work in a fast-paced environment.&lt;/p&gt;
