&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Vail Health has become the world’s most advanced mountain healthcare system. Vail Health consists of an updated 520,000-square-foot, 56-bed hospital.&amp;nbsp; This state-of-the-art facility provides exceptional care to all of our patients, with the most beautiful views in the area, located centrally in Vail. Learn more about Vail Health &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.vailhealth.org/about&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Certified Hand Therapist (CHT) – Part Time&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Opportunity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Vail Health is seeking a &lt;strong&gt;Certified Hand Therapist (CHT)&lt;/strong&gt;—either an Occupational Therapist or Physical Therapist—to support patients with upper extremity conditions through specialized, medically prescribed hand therapy. This role is responsible for delivering high‑quality clinical care and coordinating all aspects of the hand therapy program.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Schedule: Includes two 8-hour shifts and one 6-hour shift weekly, with an additional 2 hours of coverage to support operational needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Will Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluate, plan, and provide treatment for patients with upper extremity injuries or conditions to help them regain function or adapt to limitations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver patient‑centered care by interpreting evaluations and test results, and coordinating treatment plans with physicians, physician assistants, and athletic trainers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor patient progress, recommend adjustments to therapy plans, and document evaluations, goals, treatments, and outcomes in accordance with facility standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support patients returning to work by collaborating with physicians, employers, and case managers; identifying potential challenges; and recommending job site accommodations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fabricate custom thermoplastic orthoses and educate patients on proper wear, use, and care.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate and timely documentation and billing for all patient encounters.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in developing hand therapy protocols, participate in continuing education, and contribute to in‑service training for clinical staff.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support student program development and provide training to students.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage hand therapy inventory and order necessary supplies for the clinic.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure compliance with all federal, state, and local regulations, as well as certification requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain HIPAA compliance and perform additional duties as assigned.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
